OL,3,CHillsborough Law to prevent cover-ups
OL,4,C'must be all or nothing' ` campaigners
OL,6,FPrime Minister Sir Keir Starmer has
OL,7,Fpreviously pledged to introduce the so-
OL,8,Fcalled "Hillsborough Law" before this
OL,9,Fyear's anniversary of the tragedy,
OL,10,Fwhich took place on April 15 1989.
OL,12,FThe law campaigners want would
OL,13,Fintroduce a legal duty of candour on
OL,14,Fpublic authorities and officials to
OL,15,Ftell the truth and proactively co-
OL,16,Foperate with official investigations
OL,17,Fand inquiries ` with the potential for
OL,18,Fcriminal sanctions for officials or
OL,19,Forganisations which mislead or
OL,20,Fobstruct investigations.
