OL,6,FInquest has published a report after
OL,7,Fbringing together "powerful voices of
OL,8,Fbereaved families, victims and
OL,9,Fsurvivors of some of the worst
OL,10,Ffailings of public services and the
OL,11,Flegal system in the UK" to re-state
OL,12,Fthe need for a strong law.
OL,14,FIn it, Inquest director, Deborah Coles
OL,15,Fsaid the law "must be 'all or
OL,16,Fnothing', without dilution or caveat,
OL,17,Fto ensure the response to contentious
OL,18,Fdeaths, harms and grave injustices
OL,19,Fdramatically improves".
